-0.113 0 (AT&T)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 945 M
0.117 0 (Separate compilation of templates is a fundamental issue that affects the nature of C++, the organization)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 995 M
0.044 0 (and style of programs, and the direction of C++\222s future development. Language design issues of this)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1045 M
0.090 0 (magnitude must not be sacrificed to short-term implementation issues. I consider C++ without separate)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1095 M
0.040 0 (compilation of templates to be incomplete and incoherent; hence, unacceptable.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F4_50
Ji
296 1245 M
0.230 0 (Background)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1317 M
0.085 0 (C++ templates were designed with separate compilation in mind. I consider separate compilation of)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1367 M
0.126 0 (templates a fundamental and integral part of C++ just like separate compilation of non-template functions.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1417 M
-0.061 0 (The ARM reflects that view, and that view was overwhelmingly confirmed by the specific vote \(motion)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1467 M
0.110 0 (#27 in Valley Forge\) that introduced inclusion of non-inline template functions into multiple compilation)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1517 M
0.014 0 (units. Separate compilation of templates was also implicitly confirmed by the vote that added templates to)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1567 M
-0.008 0 (the working paper and by every vote to confirm the working paper over the last five years or so. In my)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1617 M
0.154 0 (opinion, changing something this fundamental to the language at the point of voting out a second CD)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1667 M
0.037 0 (would be a travesty -- even if the change had been an improvement.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F4_50
Ji
296 1767 M
0.220 0 (Modularity)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1839 M
0.067 0 (To enable efficiency comparable to hand-written code, templates are open to their environment. That is,)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1889 M
0.128 0 (names from the definition  context and user context can be used in a template. This is what makes)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1939 M
0.070 0 (templates different from traditional \(non-C\) modules and precludes the generation of code from a template)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 1989 M
0.123 0 (in isolation from its users. In other words, a template cannot \(in general\) be implemented as a \(separately)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2039 M
-0.052 0 (compiled\) piece of machine code accessed exclusively through some vector of pointers. In C++, abstract)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2089 M
0.026 0 (classes and sets of pointers to functions serve that need.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
446 2139 M
0.005 0 (This \(essential\) openness of templates makes templates vulnerable to accidental clashes between)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2189 M
0.151 0 (names used in a template definition and names from its environment. Naturally, programmers take steps)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2239 M
0.063 0 (to minimize undesirable clashes. Namespaces provides one mechanism to control context and increase)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2289 M
0.058 0 (locality. However, templates are still vulnerable to interference from global names. In particular, separate)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2339 M
0.033 0 (compilation is the only protection from macros.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
446 2389 M
0.153 0 (In general, C++ is designed with the philosophy that locality is good, that information hiding is)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2439 M
0.032 0 (good, and that the complete source of a program is not always available. Separate compilation serves as)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2489 M
0.130 0 (the most Draconian and most effective mechanism of isolating information in a program. The inclusion)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2539 M
0.079 0 (model of template compilation gives up that protection and organizational advantages of separate)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2589 M
0.024 0 (compilation in favor of a small measure of conceptual simplicity, considerable implementation simplicity,)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2639 M
0.060 0 (and some compile-time efficiency in initial implementations.)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
446 2689 M
0.025 0 (Banning separate compilation of templates would warp some programs away from proper designs)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2739 M
0.057 0 (relying on information hiding. It would also increase the pressure to compensate by providing various)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2789 M
-0.038 0 (module facilities and \223object models.\224 Such features would almost certainly be mutually incompatible,)A
; : 0 0 2391 3229 rc 0 0 0 sco F0_42
Ji
296 2839 M
0.151 0 (proprietary, and competing with standard features for the attention of programmers and designers. The)A
